ondensation to serine (rxn_017) is the reverse of serine's known retro-aldol decomposition pathway (a major decomposition route per K\u00f6rner et al. 2021). This means the equilibrium strongly disfavors serine formation under most conditions. While the concept is thermodynamically valid in principle (under very specific conditions with product removal), the literature explicitly identifies retro-aldol as a decomposition mechanism, making the forward reaction prebiotically questionable without specific activation chemistry.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_017\"],\n      \"suggestions\": [\"Consider enzyme-like mineral catalysts that could shift equilibrium; alternatively, reframe as a minor/auxiliary route rather than a primary pathway; note that Powner's phosphorylation-controlled network might stabilize the product\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_015\": 0.88,\n        \"rxn_016\": 0.90,\n        \"rxn_017\": 0.55\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.65,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.68,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.72,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.58,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.63,\n      \"feedback\": \"Inherits the fundamental problem of P9 \u2014 the glycine\u2013formaldehyde aldol condensation is thermodynamically disfavored. ZnS photocatalytic start is good but cannot rescue the problematic final step. This is the weakest pathway in the network.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_017\"],\n      \"suggestions\": [\"Replace the aldol step with a different glycine-to-serine conversion, or remove this pathway in favor of strengthening better-supported routes\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"best_pathway_id\": \"P2\",\n  \"overall_confidence\": 0.86,\n  \"network_feedback\": \"This is an excellent synthesis network for prebiotic L-serine that demonstrates deep engagement with the literature. The network's gr